  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for FEA prediction of ASTM F1717 static compression-bending performance of a non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw construct. COU1 is the validation activity itself — the FEA model ensemble (FDA, Ansys, DePuy Synthes) is compared against N=11 experimental constructs across two laboratories. All 13 V&V 40 factors assessed; one factor (Test conditions) below required level due to single test condition. Synthetic adversarial sample embedding W-AR-05 (comparator absence) via D3 undercutting: one validation result omits comparedAgainst, and the referenced experimental dataset was collected under a cannulated-screw protocol rather than the non-cannulated COU declared herein.",
