    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "Twelve of thirteen V&V 40 credibility factors meet or exceed required levels for a Model Risk Level 3, Medium-consequence COU. The single deficient factor (Test conditions, achieved level 2 vs. required level 3) is acknowledged and accepted on the basis that the single-condition ASTM F1717 protocol is consistent with regulatory precedent for Class II spinal fixation devices and that all three primary QoIs satisfy quantitative acceptance criteria with margin. The supplemental stiffness cross-check against a historical dataset provides additional confidence in the numerical framework. Overall credibility is sufficient to support the regulatory submission claim.",
